SIMPLE: unhappy
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unhappy
<hw>Un*hap"py</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Not
happy or fortunate; unfortunate; unlucky; <as>as, affairs have taken an
<ex>unhappy</ex> turn</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>In a degree miserable or wretched; not happy; sad;
sorrowful; <as>as, children render their parents <ex>unhappy</ex> by
misconduct</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Marked by infelicity; evil; calamitous; <as>as, an
<ex>unhappy</ex> day</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The <xex>unhappy</xex>
morn.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Mischievous; wanton; wicked.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Un*hap"pi*ly</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Un*hap"pi*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unharbor</ent>⟦br⟧
